The Book of Jack - by Mark Schipper

The Book of Jack was supposed to be an entertaining exploration of the name 'Jack', its origins and usage, the letter 'j' and even the sound 'dzh', but it turned into something quite a bit different...

... I am now learning web design and development using HTML/Haml, CSS/Sass, JavaScript/jQuery and Ruby on Rails. To learn all this stuff, I am also learning SQLite, Textmate, Git, iTerm, test driven development, behaviour driven development, and a host of other things. 

I should really write a colophon to describe all the tools, technologies and methodologies I am learning, which I could never have done had most of this information been proprietary.